{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make it a legal requirement for drivers to give priority to recovery vehicles",
        "additional_details": "There are estimated to be 6-8 recovery drivers killed each year whilst trying to make a living for their families. I should be able to do my job without having to worry about if I\u2019m going to get home. Too often, road users don\u2019t make any effort to slow down or move over. It doesn\u2019t take a lot to do this.",
        "background": "The Government should create a law (\u2018Martin\u2019s Law\u2019) requiring road users to move over and slow down when a recovery driver is in a live lane or hard shoulder trying to do his job and recover a vehicle.",
